22 Club: 
View Here: "http://www.22club.co.uk/"
The existing 22 Club website was analysed to identify usability and design issues that could be improved in a redesigned version of the site.

Key Issues Identified

Navigation readability
- The top navigation bar lacked strong contrast between the background and text. This reduced readability and made navigation difficult, especially on smaller screens.

Mobile responsiveness
- When the site was viewed on mobile devices, the navigation bar resized poorly. Elements became cramped and difficult to interact with.

Typography and text layout
- Large sections of text were centre aligned, which reduced readability. Consistent left-aligned text is generally easier for users to scan and read.

Content hierarchy and flow
- Information was not organised clearly, which disrupted the natural reading flow. Sections such as facilities (bar, pool, snooker, darts) appeared visually cluttered.

Visual consistency
- Some images appeared misaligned or poorly integrated into the layout. This made parts of the site feel visually inconsistent.

Unclear structure
- The “Find Us” section only contained a Google Maps embed without a clear label. Users may not immediately understand the purpose of the section.

Incomplete pages
- Some pages were empty or lacked meaningful content. This created a poor user experience and reduced trust in the site.

Backend portal exclusion
- The administrative portal was intentionally excluded from the redesign scope as it falls outside a UX/UI front-end design role.

Opportunities for Improvement
- Improve navbar contrast and visibility
- Implement mobile responsive navigation
- Use consistent typography and left-aligned text
- Improve visual hierarchy and spacing
- Clearly label sections such as location and facilities
- Maintain consistent imagery and layout design
